article.headline: Toledo 77, North Carolina-Wilmington 74
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Keonta Howell scored 20 points Saturday night to lead Toledo to a 77-74 win over UNC Wilmington. Todd Hendley's jumper with 18 seconds left cut Toledo's lead to 76-74. After Howell hit a free throw, Temi Soyebo missed a potential game-tying three-point shot as time expired. Tyrone Kent finished with 16 points and seven rebounds for Toledo (3-5), while Florentino Valencia and Justin Ingram added 11 apiece. Vladimir Kuljanin led the Seahawks (3-6) with 23 points and six rebounds, Daniel Fountain scored 16 points and Montez Downey added 13. UNC Wilmington was 32-of-52 shooting (62 percent), while the Rockets were only 27-of-59 (46 percent).
